   Special Notices:
     * NEW Available on February 1, 2002, aggregate payroll indexes for
       major industry divisions, seasonally adjusted. Get data from Create
       Customized Tables (one screen or multiple screens) or Series
       Report.
     * UPDATED Impact of the Events of September 11, 2001, on BLS Nonfarm
       Payroll Employment Series
     * Employment in Areas of Manhattan Affected by the Events of
       September 11, 2001
     * NEW CES will convert to a new industry classification system, the
       North American Industry Classification System (NAICS 2002) in June
       2003

                                                                       Top
   Get Detailed Statistics:
     * CES Data Access Tips--Quick, easy instructions on how to extract
       Employment, Hours, and Earnings data from the Current Employment
       Statistics survey
     * Most Requested Statistics--Select from lists of the most popular
       CES (National) statistics
     * Create Customized Tables (one screen)--this application (previously
       called "Public Data Query") requires a Java-enabled browser. Choose
       the data you want from BLS databases on a simple, one-screen form..
     * Create Customized Tables (multiple screens) --a form-based query
       application which allows you to obtain BLS timeseries data based on
       choices you make (previously called "Selective Access").
     * Series Report --Already know the series identifier for the
       statistic you want? Use this shortcut to retrieve your data.
     * Flat files (FTP)--For those who want it all. Download a flat file
       of the entire database or large subset of the database.
     * Historical "B" Tables--Access to Historical data for the 'B' tables
       of the Employment Situation news release provides times series data
       from the 'B' tables.

                                                                       Top
   Tables Created by BLS:

     * Historical data for the B1-B6 tables from the Employment Situation
       --for databases and spread sheets.
     * NEW Analytical Tables --present several different views of National
       CES estimates.
     * Benchmark Information --Benchmark Article and corresponding
       comparison tables, Revisions to Estimates, Question and Answer
       tables, and Bias and Net Birth/Death Model Information.
     * Tables from Employment and Earnings --Monthly Establishment Data.
     * Current Seasonal Factors --files are in ASCII format and can be
       used in data processing programs such as EXCEL or SAS.
     * Shipyard Earnings Index --Produced by CES under contract with the
       Department of Navy, Naval Sea Systems Command (NAVSEA).

   Historical data for the B1-B6 tables from the Employment Situation

     * Supporting Documentation for B1-B6 Data Files
     * Table B1 SA --Employees on nonfarm payrolls by industry, seasonally
       adjusted
     * Table B-1 NSA --Employees on nonfarm payrolls by industry, not
       seasonally adjusted
     * Table B-2 SA --Average weekly hours of production or nonsupervisory
       workers on private nonfarm payrolls by industry, seasonally
       adjusted
     * Table B-2 NSA --Average weekly hours of production or
       nonsupervisory workers on private nonfarm payrolls by industry, not
       seasonally adjusted
     * Table B-3 AHE --Average hourly earnings of production or
       nonsupervisory workers on private nonfarm payrolls by industry
     * Table B-3 AWE --Average weekly earnings of production or
       nonsupervisory workers on private nonfarm payrolls by industry
     * Table B-4 --Average hourly earnings of production or nonsupervisory
       workers on private nonfarm payrolls by industry, seasonally
       adjusted
     * Table B-5 SA --Indexes of aggregate weekly hours of production
       workers on private nonfarm payrolls by industry, seasonally
       adjusted
     * Table B-5 NSA --Indexes of aggregate weekly hours of production
       workers on private nonfarm payrolls by industry, not seasonally
       adjusted
     * Table B-6 --Diffusion indexes of employment change, seasonally
       adjusted

   ANALYTICAL TABLES

     * TABLE 1. Normal seasonal movements, estimated employment change and
       test of significance, in thousands
     * TABLE 2. Detailed industry employment ranked by change and prior
       3-month average change, in thousands, seasonally adjusted
     * TABLE 3. Employment change compared with recent averages, in
       thousands, seasonally adjusted
     * TABLE 4. Employment change from same month a year ago, in
       thousands, seasonally adjusted
     * TABLE 5. Aggregate weekly hours and payrolls, in thousands,
       seasonally adjusted
     * NEW TABLE 6. Most recent industry-specific peak and trough
       employment and change through Nov. 2001, in thousands
     * NEW TABLE 7a. Comparison with previous recessions: Employment
       change from NBER- designated peak to same number of months after
       peak, in thousands, seasonally adjusted
     * NEW TABLE 7b. Comparison with previous recessions: Percent
       employment change from NBER-designated peak to same number of
       months after peak

